   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: concussion strategy (ps: cazan please read)</span><hr size=1> Concussion is easily one of the most valuable spells in the game to an endgame/raiding wizard, as Cazan has pointed out. Its value is still great for those not at the endgame, but for those that are, it is even more powerful. <br>
<br>
More often than not, a wizard in an endgame gear is limited in damage by one thing... aggro. With IM3 cantana, kei, potg, mind wrack, flowing thought, familiars, epics, mental clarity, spell casting mastery, potions, item based non flowing thought mana regen, god rods, harvest, nuke robes, etc.. mana is no longer the limiting factor in a wizard's ability to do damage in a major encounter. In the endgame wizards have so many resources to call upon to prolong their ability to cast spells that it has become an almost non issue. We have the ability to push DPS that most other classes cannot even fathom with rains/robes/nukes being intertwined to stack their damage upon eachother. What stops those numbers from being their full potential is one thing, aggro. I cannot emphasize that enough, and your only way to control any of your aggro by your own hand is either by not nuking, or casting concussion. <br>
<br>
There is spell casting subtly and enchanter vissages, but concussion lets you manipulate your aggro in a controled manor at your whim, something no other ability in the game provides. Any wizard who does not have concussion, simply cannot understand how valuable it is. I used to think myself, that it was a waste and only for those who could not manage their aggro, then I got a bug up my ass and just did the quest (really is not that hard heh). I have made no larger mistake in my entire career as a wizard than the one to prolong the completion of this quest. <br>
<br>
If your the type of wizard, who knows how to manipulate aggro, use your epic rune, etc, even if not in an endgame guild.. you need to do this quest. If you have been debating it, stop debating, get off your ass and get the spell. This allows you to further manipulate your aggro, and to a much finer and controled degree. <br>
<br>
If your a raiding wizard, endgame or not, on any mob that has the potential to live long enough that it will come after you from you from aggro, and are actually trying to play your wizard to its full potential, then you need this spell. <br>
<br>
The wizards out there who refuse to get concussion, or who feel the spell is useless, are simply ignorant of their capabilities with it and that.. is a shame. <p><br><br><center><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=22676" target=blank><IMG SRC="http://4.65.47.107/mandosig4.jpg" border="0"></a>
